## 7. Formatting Rules

### Numbers

- Spell out one through nine, use digits for 10+
- Always use digits for technical values: "4px", "3 columns", "2 retries"
- Use commas in numbers >= 1,000
- Use "%" not "percent" in UI; spell out in prose

### Dates and Times

- Format: "February 20, 2026" in prose, "2026-02-20" in code/data
- Times: "3:00 PM EST" (12-hour with timezone)
- Relative time in UI: "2 hours ago", "Yesterday"

### Lists

- Use bullet points for unordered lists, numbered lists for sequential steps
- Start each item with a capital letter
- No periods at the end of list items unless they are complete sentences
- Keep list items parallel in structure

### Code in Documentation

- Use backticks for inline code: `componentName`
- Use fenced code blocks with language tags for multi-line code
- Include a brief comment if the code is not self-explanatory
